Salomon Brothers Inc, acting as soleunderwriter, said it is publicly offering 50,000 units of VanDusen Airport Services Co, L.P.    The offering consists of 50 mln dlrs of 12 pct seniorsubordinated notes due 1997 and 50,000 contingent paymentobligations. The notes are priced at par, or 1,000 dlrs each.    A unit has one par value note and one contingent paymentobligation. The notes are redeemable by Van Dusen after March15, 1992, Salomon said.    A payment obligation entitles the holder to receive a cashpayment under certain events, or to certain repurchase rights. Reuter&#3;